cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.GR 

The paper involves using a 3D game engine to create towers of wooden blocks and training deep feed-forward models to learn intuitive physics. This suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves generalization to new physical scenarios and real wooden blocks, indicating that artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and graphics (cs.GR) may also be relevant sub-categories.
